t: 21px;\">No</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">Yes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 42px;\">Calf pain and/or unilateral lower limb edema</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">No</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">Yes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 42px;\">PE is the most likely diagnosis</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">No</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">Yes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%; height: 21px;\">5</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Surgery, lower limb plaster cast, or bedridden &gt;3 days for acute medical condition within the last four weeks.</p>",
      "more_info_en": "<p>Interpretation:</p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\"><strong>4PEPS Score for PE</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\"><strong>Clinical probability of PE</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\"><strong>PE diagnosis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">&lt;0</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">Very low <abbr title=\"Clinical pretest probability\">CPP</abbr> (&lt;2%)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">PE can be ruled out</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">0-5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">Low CPP (2-20%)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">PE can be ruled out if D-dimer level &lt;1.0 &mu;g/mL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">6-12</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">Moderate CPP (20-65%)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">PE can be ruled out if D-dimer level &lt;0.5 &mu;g/mL OR &lt;(age x 0.01) &mu;g/mL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">&ge;13</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">High CPP (&gt;65%)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.963%;\">PE cannot be ruled out without imaging testing</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
